.TH Install-Dependencies 1 "November 2025" "docker-webhook" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
Install-Dependencies \- Install required dependencies for docker-webhook
.SH SYNOPSIS
Install-Dependencies [OPTIONS]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Installs required system packages and calls Install-Docker and Install-Rclone scripts. Ensures all dependencies for docker-webhook are present. Supports both Debian and Ubuntu systems.
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
.B -h, --help
Show usage information and exit.
.TP
.B --dry-run
Show actions without making changes.
.TP
.B --force
Force reinstallation of dependencies.
.SH USAGE
sudo ./bin/Install-Dependencies [OPTIONS]
.SH AUTHOR
NobleFactor